## "Down Down"

"Down Down" is a single by the English [rock](/Rock_music) band [Status Quo](/Status_Quo_(band)), released by [Vertigo Records](/Vertigo_Records) on 29 November 1974. The track, penned by [Francis Rossi](/Francis_Rossi) and [Bob Young](/Bob_Young_(musician)), and produced by Status Quo themselves, holds the distinction of being Status Quo's sole chart-topper on the [UK Singles Chart](/UK_Singles_Chart). It held the number one position for a week in January 1975, a fleeting moment of dominance. Both the A-side, "Down Down," and its flipside, "Nightride," were plucked from the album [On the Level](/On_the_Level), which was slated for release in 1975. The album version, a more expansive 5 minutes and 24 seconds, contrasts with the single version's more concise 3 minutes and 49 seconds.

### Song Information

The genesis of "Down Down" can be traced back to [T. Rex](/T._Rex_(band))'s debut single, "[Debora](/Debora_(song))". It was initially conceived with the title "Get Down," a name later abandoned, perhaps to preempt any confusion with [Gilbert O'Sullivan](/Gilbert_O%27Sullivan)'s similarly titled song.

Towards the twilight of his career, the influential DJ [John Peel](/John_Peel) was known to feature "Down Down" in his famously eclectic DJ sets, a testament to its enduring, if somewhat unexpected, appeal.

In 1986, co-writer [Bob Young](/Bob_Young_(musician)) revisited the track, recording a [country](/Country_music) rendition to serve as the opening number for his solo album, *In Quo Country*.

More recently, in July 2012, Status Quo put a rather commercial spin on their hit. They reworked the lyrics into a three-minute promotional jingle for the Australian supermarket chain [Coles](/Coles_Supermarkets), chanting "down down, prices are down." This saccharine iteration found its way onto television screens and [YouTube](/YouTube), notably featuring in a somewhat surreal depiction of a [mince rally](/Mince_Rallies).

The song was revisited again in 2014, this time for the band's thirty-first studio album, [Aquostic – Stripped Bare](/Aquostic_%E2%80%93_Stripped_Bare). It was performed during the ninety-minute launch event at London's [Roundhouse](/Roundhouse_(venue)) on 22 October, with the performance captured and broadcast live by [BBC Radio 2](/BBC_Radio_2) as part of their esteemed *In Concert* series.

